    <note>Bian(1) Xun [7061] Xun was a Chenliu jun Bian(1), who held office in Suzhou, liked the customs and moved his lineage there, perhaps because of his brother (or cousin) Qiu's [7316] affinal connections with the Qinghe Zhang(1) of Suzhou [or perhaps this was a result of the move]. He used his father's yin to enter service. Su's [7317] grandson, Sun(1) Mian's [8118] and Lu(5) Gui's [7049] brother-in-law, Lu(5) Dian's [8098] and Lu(5) Zhuan's [7297] father-in-law (sons of Lu(5) Gui [7049]). Brother of the mother-in-law of Hu(1) Su's [8064] son, Zongyao [3400], and of the grandmother-in-law of Wu(3) Xiaoneng's [1972]. His second daughter became a buddhist nun. Lu Dian, WJ, 14.1a. CBD, 5, 4288-9.</note>
